{"data":{"page":{"id":"38dac205-2488-5ea8-b2a4-6ab8a70dd368","html":"<p class=\"align-center\">\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://github.com/gazpachu/opencv-box2d-race\" target=\"_blank\">Car race source code</a>\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://github.com/gazpachu/opencv-box2d-platformer\" target=\"_blank\">Platformer source code</a>\n</p>\n<p>This project was so cool. It was about loading a track and the obstacles from a real drawing and then playing a car race in that track in the computer!</p>\n<p>To capture the shapes from the paper, I used a webcam and the OpenCV library. These shapes were then transformed into Box2d bodies and added to the physics world in the app.</p>\n<p>The cars and the rest of the logic was all C++ and OpenFrameworks. All the captured shapes were static bodies that the cars could collide with. There was a marker also to define the start/end point.</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 612px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/647e98799a98d1c7f5a71e2a0997a914/7de53/1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/647e98799a98d1c7f5a71e2a0997a914/e250e/1.jpg 500w,\n/static/647e98799a98d1c7f5a71e2a0997a914/7de53/1.jpg 612w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 2000px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"3\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/2fdbcca96aad1d01ff5e00cf3ef5a137/b899f/3.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2fdbcca96aad1d01ff5e00cf3ef5a137/2d0bc/3.jpg 500w,\n/static/2fdbcca96aad1d01ff5e00cf3ef5a137/8b643/3.jpg 1000w,\n/static/2fdbcca96aad1d01ff5e00cf3ef5a137/b899f/3.jpg 2000w,\n/static/2fdbcca96aad1d01ff5e00cf3ef5a137/7bd7a/3.jpg 3000w,\n/static/2fdbcca96aad1d01ff5e00cf3ef5a137/734eb/3.jpg 3264w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p>Later on, I also started to play with the idea of using characters rather than cars and platforms rather than a track. The idea was that the user would draw the platforms and the characters in the paper and the app would load all this information into the app…</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1000px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 71.8%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/e7e0e57dc562e732a4266c006bcea0e0/877ff/2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e7e0e57dc562e732a4266c006bcea0e0/d2504/2.jpg 500w,\n/static/e7e0e57dc562e732a4266c006bcea0e0/877ff/2.jpg 1000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>","fields":{"prefix":"2013"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Draw a car race","categories":"wcrs prototype kinect opencv box2d openframeworks animation design installation inverted open-source","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/fe2542349f5a0249766ece3b110a10cd/445d9/logo.png"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/car-race/","source":"work"}}